♪ 'Cause Brandon wants to find
a girl to call his own. ♪

39:08.304 --> 39:11.307
(cheering and applause)

39:11.390 --> 39:12.641
{\an1}Wasn't that great,
everybody?

39:12.725 --> 39:13.768
Brenda and Kelly were up

39:13.851 --> 39:14.935
{\an3}all night writing and
choreographing that one.

39:15.019 --> 39:15.978
Good job, guys.

39:16.062 --> 39:17.772
{\an1}I just want you to know
that was not my idea.

39:17.855 --> 39:19.231
Hey, I'm not complaining.

39:19.315 --> 39:20.941
You guys want to get up there
and make fools of yourselves,

39:21.025 --> 39:21.984
be my guest.

39:22.068 --> 39:23.110
{\an3}Thanks for
being here.

39:23.194 --> 39:24.779
It's been a great year
and, uh...

39:24.862 --> 39:26.155
Not so fast, Davey.

39:26.238 --> 39:29.909
{\an3}What retrospective would be
complete without an award

39:29.992 --> 39:32.995
{\an3}to West Beverly's #1
song-and-dance man, huh?

39:33.079 --> 39:33.996
Hit it, Gary.

39:34.080 --> 39:34.622
What's he doing?

39:34.705 --> 39:36.791
You'll see.

39:36.874 --> 39:39.335
(music playing)

39:39.418 --> 39:41.837
(crowd cheering)

39:49.220 --> 39:50.971
Oh, this is from
the spring dance.

39:51.055 --> 39:52.973
Yeah, the pre-Donna era.

39:53.057 --> 39:54.308
You guys, this is great.

39:54.391 --> 39:55.684
I missed most of it
because I came late that night.

39:55.768 --> 39:58.687
Yeah.

39:58.771 --> 40:01.023
I missed most of it, too.

40:06.070 --> 40:07.154
Dylan, this is so beautiful.

40:07.238 --> 40:08.155
Do you know

40:08.239 --> 40:10.866
why I'm so lucky?

40:12.076 --> 40:13.994
Why?

40:14.078 --> 40:16.080
{\an3}How many girls get to have
sex for the first time

40:16.163 --> 40:17.832
with someone they love?

40:17.915 --> 40:19.166
I don't know.

40:19.250 --> 40:21.669
{\an1}I've never really taken
an opinion poll.

40:21.752 --> 40:23.754
Mm.

40:26.340 --> 40:28.342
{\an3}DWhoo!

40:28.425 --> 40:29.343
Dylan, stop!

40:29.426 --> 40:31.846
Put me down!

40:31.929 --> 40:32.680
{\an3}I'm sorry.

40:32.763 --> 40:34.473
{\an1}I just can't
control myself.

40:34.557 --> 40:35.558
{\an3}Well, don't
fight it.

40:35.808 --> 40:38.811
We are in the room.

40:38.894 --> 40:40.980
We certainly are.

40:45.109 --> 40:48.821
(music playing)

40:48.904 --> 40:49.738
(crowd cheering)

41:06.964 --> 41:10.050
Th-th-th-that's all, folks!

41:26.859 --> 41:28.861
{\an1}You got
a standing ovation.

41:28.944 --> 41:31.530
{\an1}Doesn't that count
for something?

41:31.614 --> 41:34.033
{\an3}I just feel kind of
burned out, that's all.

41:34.116 --> 41:35.409
Well, of course you do.

41:35.492 --> 41:36.577
I mean, anybody would

41:36.660 --> 41:39.205
{\an1}with the schedule you've
