Come on, David,
we're putting out this issue

56:02.525 --> 56:04.569
as a tribute to Scott.

56:04.652 --> 56:05.987
Why?

56:06.071 --> 56:08.656
So people can glance at it and
then throw it in the garbage?

56:08.740 --> 56:12.118
No, so people can get some kind
of an idea as to who he was.

56:12.202 --> 56:14.245
Look,(microphone feedback)

56:14.329 --> 56:17.165
He was a jerk who blew himself
away, that's who he was.

56:17.248 --> 56:19.250
You don't know, you left early.

56:19.334 --> 56:22.128
You missed out on the fun part
when he picked up a loaded gun

56:22.212 --> 56:23.630
and twirled it around
like Wyatt Earp.

56:23.713 --> 56:26.299
You weren't there
to see him goof up

56:26.382 --> 56:27.634
and shoot himself
and bleed all over

56:27.717 --> 56:28.968
his mom's Persian rug.

56:29.052 --> 56:30.303
David, the microphone is on.

56:30.386 --> 56:32.472
I don't care.

56:32.555 --> 56:35.809
No one gave a rat's ass
about Scott until he died.

56:35.892 --> 56:37.977
And I was the worst one of all.

56:38.061 --> 56:40.146
He was my best friend
and I dropped him

56:40.230 --> 56:42.941
because he wasn't cool
like you or Kelly or Steve.

56:43.024 --> 56:44.442
David.

56:45.860 --> 56:47.487
So they're looking at me.

56:47.570 --> 56:48.655
So what?

56:48.738 --> 56:51.991
They've been looking
at me for days, Brandon.

56:52.075 --> 56:54.119
I can't even walk through
the hall without somebody

56:54.202 --> 56:56.996
in my face trying to cheer me up
like they're my new best friend.

56:57.080 --> 56:59.582
Well, what about
my old best friend?

57:01.918 --> 57:03.378
It doesn't matter
what you write about him

57:03.461 --> 57:04.671
in that paper, Brandon.

57:04.754 --> 57:05.964
It doesn't matter
what you say

57:06.047 --> 57:07.340
about somebody
once they're gone.

57:07.423 --> 57:10.468
What matters is how you treat
them when they're still here.

57:15.598 --> 57:17.642
(phone ringing)

57:22.105 --> 57:23.857
Hello?

57:23.940 --> 57:25.859
Oh, hi, Donna.

57:25.942 --> 57:27.735
Well, you can ask him yourself.

57:27.819 --> 57:30.155
{\an1}She wants to know
how you're feeling.

57:31.447 --> 57:33.408
I'm starting to come around.

57:34.409 --> 57:36.578
Just let me know
when you're done.

57:40.957 --> 57:43.418
(phone ringing)

57:45.461 --> 57:47.338
Hello?

57:47.422 --> 57:48.339
KELLY (on phone):
Hi.

57:48.423 --> 57:48.756
Hi, what's up?

57:48.840 --> 57:49.757
Not too much.

57:49.841 --> 57:50.717
I'm just getting ready to go out
for my manicure.

57:50.800 --> 57:51.718
I wanted to check in.

57:51.801 --> 57:53.761
I also wanted to say

57:53.845 --> 57:57.432
that I'll never talk about
your bank account again.

57:57.515 --> 57:59.684
It's no one's business,
especially mine.

57:59.767 --> 58:01.561
I appreciate the call.

58:01.644 --> 58:03.188
See you in a couple of hours?

58:03.271 --> 58:05.356
With bells on.

58:05.440 --> 58:08.067
Bye.

58:08.151 --> 58:10.153
(dial tone, phone beeps off)

58:27.587 --> 58:28.630
{\an1}So there I am sitting
at the Senior Breakfast,

58:28.713 --> 58:32.467
and I'm thinking
about Minnesota.

58:32.550 --> 58:35.678
{\an1}And I wanted to say,
"Hey, everybody, I got in."

58:35.762 --> 58:39.474
But something held me back.

58:39.557 --> 58:44.103
Maybe you thought they would
try and convince you to stay?

58:44.187 --> 58:45.730
{\an1}Or maybe I was scared
that they wouldn't.

58:46.856 --> 58:48.858
What do you want to do?

58:51.736 --> 58:54.614
I'm torn.

58:54.697 --> 58:55.740
My surefire remedy
in a case like this

58:55.823 --> 58:58.117
is to just flip a coin.

58:58.201 --> 59:00.745
{\an1}Is that what you did
with me and Kelly?

59:03.706 --> 59:04.749
{\an1}Sorry, that didn't
come out right.

59:04.832 --> 59:06.292
You don't have to answer that.

59:06.376 --> 59:07.752
No, I want to.

59:07.835 --> 59:09.671
Because what I think
you're really asking me is,

59:09.754 --> 59:12.423
if there were no Kelly, would
you and I still be together?

59:14.384 --> 59:15.802
The thought has
crossed my mind.

59:17.887 --> 59:20.473
The truth is...

59:20.556 --> 59:22.684
I don't know.

59:22.767 --> 59:23.810
I loved you more
than I ever thought

59:23.893 --> 59:26.813
I could love anybody,
maybe that was the problem.

59:28.773 --> 59:31.693
It was just too intense
for both of us.

59:31.776 --> 59:35.280
{\an1}Yeah, I guess right
from the start it was...

59:35.363 --> 59:36.656
it was just so volatile.

59:36.739 --> 59:39.284
Look, do you wanna take a walk
on the beach or something?

59:39.367 --> 59:41.452
Oh, yeah, check out the homeless
people? That'll be great.

59:41.536 --> 59:42.662
{\an1}Dylan, I don't know
what happened up there!

59:42.745 --> 59:44.163
That's right,
you don't!

59:44.247 --> 59:45.081
If you'dExcuse me.nish...!

59:45.164 --> 59:47.041
I have a knack for
interrupting things.

59:47.125 --> 59:48.376
I'm real good at interrupting

59:48.459 --> 59:48.960
because I've had just
about enough noise

59:49.043 --> 59:49.836
for one night, okay?!

59:49.919 --> 59:51.713
{\an1}Excuse me, can you
get me a taxi, please?

59:51.796 --> 59:52.714
Forget the taxi!

59:52.797 --> 59:53.881
No, I want a taxi!

59:53.965 --> 59:56.467
No, just come on, damn it!

59:56.551 --> 59:58.720
Stop yelling at me!

01:00:03.266 --> 01:00:05.184
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

01:00:05.268 --> 01:00:06.686
Just let me go.

01:00:06.769 --> 01:00:09.188
Brenda, I'm an idiot.
Please don't leave.

01:00:09.272 --> 01:00:09.731
You're scaring me!

01:00:09.814 --> 01:00:13.318
I'm sorry.

01:00:15.486 --> 01:00:16.863
Dylan, what happened?

01:00:16.946 --> 01:00:20.366
He just gets to me.

01:00:20.450 --> 01:00:22.368
He always gets to me.

01:00:22.452 --> 01:00:25.038
I don't know what
I'm supposed to...

01:00:25.121 --> 01:00:27.123
(moans)

01:00:27.915 --> 01:00:28.833
It's okay.

01:00:28.916 --> 01:00:30.918
(sobbing)

01:00:49.937 --> 01:00:51.856
{\an1}We did have some
good time, though.

01:00:51.939 --> 01:00:55.401
{\an1}Like that week in Baja
when you taught me how to surf

01:00:55.485 --> 01:00:56.652
and we danced all night.

01:00:56.736 --> 01:00:57.862
Not all night.

01:01:00.615 --> 01:01:02.033
{\an1}Too bad my dad
couldn't understand

01:01:02.116 --> 01:01:03.785
what we weHmm.ll about.

01:01:04.994 --> 01:01:05.912
Where is she?

01:01:05.995 --> 01:01:08.414
She doesn't want to see you.

01:01:08.498 --> 01:01:09.832
That's too bad.

01:01:09.916 --> 01:01:13.419
You tell her to get her
things and come out here.

01:01:13.503 --> 01:01:15.088
I'm sorry, I can't do that.

01:01:15.171 --> 01:01:17.090
I'm not leaving, Daddy.

01:01:17.173 --> 01:01:19.801
You get your bags young
lady, we're going home.

01:01:19.884 --> 01:01:22.220
{\an1}No.

01:01:22.303 --> 01:01:23.971
Not until you accept Dylan
as part of my life.

01:01:26.557 --> 01:01:27.975
We'll talk about it at home.

01:01:28.059 --> 01:01:31.562
That's not good enough.

01:01:36.692 --> 01:01:39.487
Brenda, you come out
h(door closes).

01:01:39.904 --> 01:01:43.449
So what're you gonna do?

01:01:43.533 --> 01:01:45.660
You gonna go down and drag
her out kicking and screaming?

01:01:45.743 --> 01:01:47.286
That's what this has come to.

01:01:47.370 --> 01:01:50.790
Dylan, whatever this
has come to,

01:01:50.873 --> 01:01:54.419
it hasn't come to that.

01:01:55.753 --> 01:01:56.963
I guess that was
the beginning of the end.

01:01:57.046 --> 01:02:00.967
Yeah, for us to live
together at that point

01:02:01.050 --> 01:02:01.926
was a huge mistake.

01:02:02.009 --> 01:02:03.803
{\an1}And you got so
incredibly offended

01:02:03.886 --> 01:02:06.639
{\an1}when I tried to clean
this place up.

01:02:06.722 --> 01:02:08.933
Well, hey, dust adds
a little character.

01:02:10.059 --> 01:02:11.978
{\an1}I guess Kelly
doesn't mind it, huh?

01:02:14.772 --> 01:02:16.441
I guess not.

01:02:16.524 --> 01:02:18.568
{\an1}Was that her
on the phone before?

01:02:18.651 --> 01:02:21.362
Yeah.

01:02:21.446 --> 01:02:23.030
{\an1}Why didn't you
tell her I was here?

01:02:23.114 --> 01:02:24.949
She didn't ask.

01:02:27.452 --> 01:02:29.412
But I have a question
for you, Bren.

01:02:31.414 --> 01:02:32.832
Why'd you come over here?

01:02:36.586 --> 01:02:38.963
I guess I wanted
to say good-bye.

01:02:39.046 --> 01:02:41.674
In private.

01:02:41.757 --> 01:02:43.050
How private?

01:02:46.971 --> 01:02:49.682
(doorbell chimes)

01:02:49.765 --> 01:02:51.142
Ooh, saved by the bell.

01:02:51.225 --> 01:02:53.144
IRIS:
Dylan, are you there?

01:02:53.227 --> 01:02:55.730
{\an3}It figures.

01:02:55.813 --> 01:02:57.398
IsWho else?s?

01:03:04.489 --> 01:03:05.865
{\an1}Do you mind telling me
exactly what it is

01:03:05.948 --> 01:03:08.826
you have against the telephone?

01:03:08.910 --> 01:03:11.871
I'd rather you told me
what it is you have against me.

01:03:11.954 --> 01:03:14.874
That was a very chilly reception
you gave me last night.

01:03:14.957 --> 01:03:17.543
I thought it over,
and it's come to this:

01:03:17.627 --> 01:03:19.378
my bags are packed.

01:03:19.462 --> 01:03:20.755
And either the taxi takes me

01:03:20.838 --> 01:03:22.757
straight to your
graduation ceremony

01:03:22.840 --> 01:03:24.550
or to the airport.

01:03:24.634 --> 01:03:25.635
It's up to you.

01:03:25.718 --> 01:03:29.055
Mom, the graduation,
it doesn't start for 90 minutes.

01:03:31.807 --> 01:03:34.894
I guess I'm still
on Hawaiian time.

01:03:36.646 --> 01:03:38.397
Come on in.

01:03:38.481 --> 01:03:40.525
Say hello to Brenda.

01:03:40.608 --> 01:03:41.984
Brenda!

01:03:42.068 --> 01:03:43.402
{\an1}Iris, hi.
Good to see you.

01:03:43.486 --> 01:03:44.612
Well, it's good to see you.

01:03:44.695 --> 01:03:46.614
I hope I wasn't
interrupting anything.

01:03:46.697 --> 01:03:49.158
{\an1}No, actually
I was just leaving.

01:03:49.242 --> 01:03:51.619
{\an1}I just came to get some
advice from an old friend.

01:03:51.702 --> 01:03:53.621
Bye. I'll see you in 90 minutes.

01:03:53.704 --> 01:03:55.581
Bye.

01:03:59.835 --> 01:04:01.045
KELLY:
Mom.

01:04:01.128 --> 01:04:02.755
I'm getting ready to head over.

01:04:02.838 --> 01:04:03.923
Look for me in the "T's."

01:04:04.006 --> 01:04:05.550
I'll see you there.

01:04:05.633 --> 01:04:07.802
Oh, I'm so proud of you.

01:04:07.885 --> 01:04:08.761
{\an3}Thank you.

01:04:08.844 --> 01:04:10.429
Are you proud of me?

01:04:10.513 --> 01:04:12.431
Yes, you better be.

01:04:12.515 --> 01:04:13.808
You know, she's
getting so big

01:04:13.891 --> 01:04:15.810
and I have known you
your whole life, Erin.

01:04:15.893 --> 01:04:18.771
Just think, if I hadn't
stayed here this summer

01:04:18.854 --> 01:04:20.565
to help you with
the baby, then...

01:04:20.648 --> 01:04:22.066
Dylan and I may have
never gotten together.

01:04:22.149 --> 01:04:24.944
See, sometimes things
do work out.

01:04:25.027 --> 01:04:29.407
Yep, although that
living together idea,

01:04:29.490 --> 01:04:30.783
you don't have to
worry about it.

01:04:30.866 --> 01:04:31.200
It's not in the cards.

01:04:31.284 --> 01:04:31.951
What did he say?

01:04:32.034 --> 01:04:34.120
I didn't even
bring it up.

01:04:34.203 --> 01:04:36.789
I mean, I know he
cares about me,

01:04:36.872 --> 01:04:39.792
but he really is a loner.

01:04:39.875 --> 01:04:42.128
He reminds me of your father.

01:04:42.211 --> 01:04:44.797
{\an1}Let's just hope he
doesn't turn out to be

01:04:44.880 --> 01:04:47.466
{\an1}so much of an emotional
no-show.

01:04:47.550 --> 01:04:49.760
Well, at least Dad called.

01:04:49.844 --> 01:04:52.138
{\an1}Yeah, he should've
been here.

01:04:52.221 --> 01:04:54.765
Well, I think I know what
I'll major in in college.

01:04:54.849 --> 01:04:56.183
{\an3}Psychology.

01:04:56.267 --> 01:04:58.311
I may join you.

01:04:58.394 --> 01:04:59.478
I'll see you over there.

01:04:59.562 --> 01:05:01.814
Wish me luck.

01:05:01.897 --> 01:05:04.650
BRENDA:
<i>Why are you wearing a tie?</i>

01:05:04.734 --> 01:05:07.361
This is a very
solemn occasion.

01:05:07.445 --> 01:05:08.988
I can't believe this
day has finally come.

01:05:09.071 --> 01:05:09.655
Yeah, believe it.

01:05:09.739 --> 01:05:12.700
It's time for the big sayonara.

01:05:12.783 --> 01:05:14.952
{\an3}Yeah.

01:05:22.418 --> 01:05:23.210
We've been
through a lot together

01:05:23.294 --> 01:05:25.588
over the past three years.

01:05:25.671 --> 01:05:27.506
Ah, it's been a piece of cake.

01:05:27.590 --> 01:05:28.799
(scoffs)

01:05:28.883 --> 01:05:32.011
{\an1}Maybe for you, Mr. Confident,
Mr. I've Got It Wired.

01:05:32.094 --> 01:05:34.263
Come on, Bren.

01:05:34.347 --> 01:05:38.684
When we first moved here,
I was pretty spooked.

01:05:38.768 --> 01:05:41.354
That's not how
I remember it.

01:05:41.437 --> 01:05:43.356
I miss Minneapolis.

01:05:43.439 --> 01:05:46.317
No, you don't.

01:05:46.400 --> 01:05:48.152
{\an3}Yeah, I do.

01:05:49.236 --> 01:05:51.906
Nothing was this complicated.

01:05:57.453 --> 01:05:59.497
Brandon, are we going
to make it here?

01:05:59.580 --> 01:06:02.792
Well, the houses are bigger,
the weather's warmer,

01:06:02.875 --> 01:06:05.711
but it doesn't mean they've
cracked the meaning of life,

01:06:05.795 --> 01:06:08.172
know what I mean?

01:06:08.255 --> 01:06:09.799
Yeah, I know.

01:06:15.262 --> 01:06:19.266
{\an1}Yes, I always was a sage,
even as a wee young laddie.

01:06:19.350 --> 01:06:20.559
You know what
else you are?

01:06:20.643 --> 01:06:21.560
(laughs)

01:06:21.644 --> 01:06:22.937
If you can't say
something nice...

01:06:23.020 --> 01:06:25.356
Seriously,
Brandon.

01:06:25.439 --> 01:06:27.525
Okay, Bren, what else am I?

01:06:28.693 --> 01:06:32.530
No matter how crazed or bent
out of shape I ever got,

01:06:32.613 --> 01:06:35.741
you were always there for
me and I'll never forget it.

01:06:35.825 --> 01:06:37.993
You really are
my best friend.

01:06:41.664 --> 01:06:43.833
{\an1}Well, I hope
I always will be.

01:07:11.235 --> 01:07:15.114
{\an4}STEVE:
I can't believe my mom's
here signing autographs.

01:07:15.197 --> 01:07:16.615
And there's my father.

01:07:16.699 --> 01:07:17.825
You like
your dad.

01:07:17.908 --> 01:07:20.619
Yeah, but did he have to bring
the Wicked Witch of the North

01:07:20.703 --> 01:07:22.121
{\an1}and the three flying
monkey children?

01:07:22.204 --> 01:07:23.456
Well, at least he came.

01:07:23.539 --> 01:07:24.582
Yeah, Steve,

01:07:24.665 --> 01:07:25.791
just click your heels
together three times

01:07:25.875 --> 01:07:27.668
and you'll be home
before you know it.

01:07:27.752 --> 01:07:28.961
{\an1}Yeah, well, speaking
of heels, big guy,

01:07:29.044 --> 01:07:30.796
{\an1}those are some
pretty kicking boots.

01:07:30.880 --> 01:07:32.256
{\an1}What did they set you back,
about 800 bucks?

01:07:32.339 --> 01:07:33.340
Just a graduation
present.

01:07:33.424 --> 01:07:35.426
Your mom get you those?

01:07:35.509 --> 01:07:37.303
Steve, what does it
matter where I got 'em

01:07:37.386 --> 01:07:38.304
or how much
they cost?

01:07:38.387 --> 01:07:39.430
They're just
boots, all right?

01:07:46.437 --> 01:07:49.648
So how are you doing?

01:07:49.732 --> 01:07:50.816
I'm psyched.

01:07:50.900 --> 01:07:52.651
{\an1}I made some final adjustments
on my speech

01:07:52.735 --> 01:07:55.362
and if my throat holds out,
I'll be great.

01:07:55.446 --> 01:07:57.865
Good, good,
glad to hear it.

01:07:57.948 --> 01:07:58.407
I'd better get some water.

01:07:58.491 --> 01:08:00.367
I'll be right back.

01:08:03.579 --> 01:08:04.622
{\an1}KELLY (sing-songy):
Donna.

01:08:04.705 --> 01:08:06.165
{\an1}I just wanted
to wish you good luck.

01:08:06.248 --> 01:08:07.792
What's the matter?

01:08:07.875 --> 01:08:08.834
Well, when I think

01:08:08.918 --> 01:08:11.796
if it wasn't for you and
Brandon and everyone,

01:08:11.879 --> 01:08:14.673
I wouldn't
even be here.

01:08:14.757 --> 01:08:17.676
I love you, too.

01:08:17.760 --> 01:08:20.220
Hey, hey, hey, can I
get in on this action?

01:08:20.304 --> 01:08:22.223
{\an1}Well, that's
a major mood swing.

01:08:22.305 --> 01:08:23.765
Yeah, well, I just
talked to Ms. Temaka

01:08:23.849 --> 01:08:25.725
and it seems that I got
the second highest grade

01:08:25.810 --> 01:08:26.977
on my chemistry exam.

01:08:27.060 --> 01:08:28.729
The one you thought you flunked?

01:08:28.813 --> 01:08:30.981
Guess that says something
for misnumbering.

01:08:31.064 --> 01:08:32.483
Guess so.

01:08:32.566 --> 01:08:33.692
{\an1}Oh, come here,
you guys.

01:08:33.776 --> 01:08:35.361
We're graduating!

01:08:37.404 --> 01:08:40.533
{\an1}Hey, Andrea, good
luck on that speech.

01:08:40.616 --> 01:08:41.742
Thank you.

01:08:41.826 --> 01:08:43.828
(chuckles)

01:08:48.541 --> 01:08:50.459
{\an1}I'm real proud
of you, son.

01:08:54.796 --> 01:08:57.716
{\an1}And if it takes the
pressure off, I just want you

01:08:57.800 --> 01:09:01.261
to know that you don't have
to go to college on my account.

01:09:01.345 --> 01:09:03.848
From here on out, you got
to do what's right for you.

01:09:04.932 --> 01:09:08.644
drum roll

01:09:14.024 --> 01:09:17.069
(fanfare playing)

01:09:27.621 --> 01:09:30.374
It's show time!

01:09:30.457 --> 01:09:31.375
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

01:09:31.457 --> 01:09:33.252
Break a leg, chief.

01:09:33.335 --> 01:09:34.252
Thanks, ace.

01:09:34.336 --> 01:09:36.380
Let's do it.

01:10:04.742 --> 01:10:08.370
♪ ♪

01:10:24.887 --> 01:10:26.931
(crowd applauding)

01:10:33.771 --> 01:10:37.149
{\an1}Ladies and gentlemen, may
I present the graduating class

01:10:37.232 --> 01:10:38.359
of nineteen hundred
and ninety-three.

01:11:09.264 --> 01:11:09.682
Andrea, what's the matter?

01:11:09.765 --> 01:11:12.309
I lost my speech.

01:11:12.393 --> 01:11:15.312
H-Hey, Andrea,
don't worry about it.

01:11:15.396 --> 01:11:16.689
You've been over
it so many times

01:11:16.772 --> 01:11:17.523
I'm sure you have it
memorized by now.

01:11:17.606 --> 01:11:19.692
I'm glad that you're
so sure about it

01:11:19.775 --> 01:11:21.610
because I am a complete
and total blank.

01:11:34.957 --> 01:11:37.668
And so I am honored to introduce

01:11:37.751 --> 01:11:41.171
valedictorian
of the class of 1993.

01:11:41.255 --> 01:11:41.630
Ugh!

01:11:41.714 --> 01:11:43.507
I'm seeing spots.

01:11:43.590 --> 01:11:44.758
I am hyperventilating.

01:11:44.842 --> 01:11:46.844
Maybe if you put your head
between your knees.

01:11:46.927 --> 01:11:48.262
{\an1}I'd rather put my tail
between my legs.

01:11:48.345 --> 01:11:49.596
{\an3}Andrea.

01:11:49.680 --> 01:11:52.266
Brandon, I am going to be the
laughingstock of Beverly Hills.

01:11:52.349 --> 01:11:54.226
Nobody is going
to laugh at you.

01:11:54.309 --> 01:11:55.436
Right, they're just going
to throw things at me.

01:11:55.519 --> 01:11:57.604
All right,
knock it off.

01:11:57.688 --> 01:11:58.856
That's enough.

01:11:58.939 --> 01:12:00.232
You're not going to wimp
out on me, you hear?

01:12:00.315 --> 01:12:01.900
On <i>you?</i>

01:12:01.984 --> 01:12:03.027
Damn right
on me.

01:12:03.110 --> 01:12:04.903
I helped you work on
that speech for hours

01:12:04.987 --> 01:12:06.697
and I've listened to
you agonize for years

01:12:06.780 --> 01:12:07.948
over your grade
point average

01:12:08.032 --> 01:12:09.199
and your
permanent record

01:12:09.283 --> 01:12:10.909
and I'm not going
to let you blow this.

01:12:10.993 --> 01:12:12.703
Now, you've practically
got a photographic memory,

01:12:12.786 --> 01:12:14.913
so you get yourself
together, you get up there,

01:12:14.997 --> 01:12:16.373
and you use it,
you hear me?

01:12:16.457 --> 01:12:18.751
{\an1}MEYERS:
As the faculty advisor...

01:12:18.834 --> 01:12:19.793
Thanks, Brandon.

01:12:19.877 --> 01:12:21.920
You're welcome.

01:12:22.004 --> 01:12:24.548
Um, j-just one thing....

01:12:24.631 --> 01:12:26.550
Do you remember
how my speech started?

01:12:26.633 --> 01:12:29.470
And so without
further ado,

01:12:29.553 --> 01:12:32.639
let us all welcome
Andrea Zuckerman,

01:12:32.723 --> 01:12:35.267
valedictorian,

01:12:35.350 --> 01:12:37.936
class of 1993.

01:12:57.539 --> 01:12:59.625
Thank you...

01:12:59.708 --> 01:13:00.626
(microphone feeds back)

01:13:00.709 --> 01:13:01.627
...Mr. Meyers,

01:13:01.710 --> 01:13:04.296
Ms. Teasley, uh,
fellow graduates,

01:13:04.380 --> 01:13:06.924
ladies and gentlemen.

01:13:07.007 --> 01:13:11.804
{\an1}Uh, today we stand here united
as a class.

01:13:11.887 --> 01:13:16.767
Tomorrow we go our separate ways
as individuals...

01:13:16.850 --> 01:13:20.437
on our own... i-individually.

01:13:20.521 --> 01:13:21.855
{\an3}We...

01:13:21.939 --> 01:13:23.857
we do this

01:13:23.941 --> 01:13:27.486
to follow the paths...
unfathomable paths

01:13:27.569 --> 01:13:29.488
which weave
before us...

01:13:29.571 --> 01:13:30.823
Oh, no.

01:13:30.906 --> 01:13:31.824
What's the matter?

01:13:31.907 --> 01:13:33.826
She went back to
the old version.

01:13:33.909 --> 01:13:35.285
(chuckles)

01:13:35.369 --> 01:13:38.330
We do so with the certainty...

01:13:38.413 --> 01:13:40.999
with the certainty...

01:13:41.083 --> 01:13:42.292
(sighs)

01:13:42.376 --> 01:13:43.877
...that we don't have
the faintest idea

01:13:43.961 --> 01:13:44.753
what we're doing at all.

01:13:44.837 --> 01:13:48.173
(laughter)

01:13:48.257 --> 01:13:49.550
(applause)

01:13:52.719 --> 01:13:54.847
Which could be
a very frightening prospect

01:13:54.930 --> 01:13:56.974
in a world where the...

01:13:57.057 --> 01:13:59.184
in a world
where the boundaries of nations

01:13:59.268 --> 01:14:02.187
and the balance of nature
can change overnight,

01:14:02.271 --> 01:14:06.108
except that the years that
we have spent at West Beverly

01:14:06.191 --> 01:14:09.862
have given us the foundation
to face that future.

01:14:09.945 --> 01:14:12.865
We haven't just learned
facts and figures,

01:14:12.948 --> 01:14:14.700
{\an1}logic
and reasoning skills,

01:14:14.783 --> 01:14:19.663
{\an1}but we have learned the value
of friendship...

01:14:19.746 --> 01:14:22.040
friendship, loyalty, and love,

01:14:22.124 --> 01:14:25.335
which will not be diminished
just because we may not

01:14:25.419 --> 01:14:26.712
end up together.

01:14:26.795 --> 01:14:32.426
The memories that we have shared
will not go away

01:14:32.509 --> 01:14:34.386
simply because we do.

01:14:34.469 --> 01:14:38.265
So even if the future
does not always meet

01:14:38.348 --> 01:14:40.392
our expectations

01:14:40.475 --> 01:14:41.768
or the fates
are cruel

01:14:41.852 --> 01:14:43.812
to us at times,

01:14:43.896 --> 01:14:47.024
no one...

01:14:47.107 --> 01:14:50.569
can ever take this moment
from me.

01:14:50.652 --> 01:14:54.781
From me, from you,
from any of us.

01:14:56.783 --> 01:15:01.788
No one can ever take away

01:15:01.872 --> 01:15:04.041
this moment in time.

01:15:04.124 --> 01:15:05.918
(applause)

01:15:30.692 --> 01:15:34.404
COACH CHAPMAN:
Gary Achatell.

01:15:34.488 --> 01:15:36.031
Michael Anderson.

01:15:38.033 --> 01:15:39.952
Ross Anderson.

01:15:40.035 --> 01:15:42.412
You know, they don't really
give you your diploma now.

01:15:42.496 --> 01:15:43.789
{\an1}It's just a blank
piece of paper.

01:15:43.872 --> 01:15:44.831
So does that mean
you don't want it?

01:15:44.915 --> 01:15:47.125
Are you crazy?

01:15:47.209 --> 01:15:49.127
Come on.ng)

01:15:50.879 --> 01:15:53.257
{\an4}STEVE:
Look out, your dad just
took out the video camera.

01:15:53.340 --> 01:15:53.799
DAVID:
Oh, you know how dads are.

01:15:53.882 --> 01:15:56.802
Not really.

01:15:58.095 --> 01:16:00.764
He didn't even have the
courtesy to call this time.

01:16:02.724 --> 01:16:05.811
He had some woman who
claimed to be his secretary

01:16:05.894 --> 01:16:07.980
call and leave
a message for me...

01:16:10.232 --> 01:16:13.443
"Your father's very sorry,

01:16:13.527 --> 01:16:16.780
but he'll make it up
to you next time."

01:16:16.863 --> 01:16:18.865
{\an1}Kel, you gotta believe
there'll be a next time.

01:16:23.870 --> 01:16:24.871
Bradley Luganis.

01:16:24.955 --> 01:16:26.707
(applause)

01:16:26.790 --> 01:16:29.543
Donna's up next.pe.

01:16:30.919 --> 01:16:34.214
Donna Martin.

01:16:40.137 --> 01:16:41.722
I don't intend
to sleep with you.

01:16:41.805 --> 01:16:46.018
Oh, oh-oh-oh,
it's-it's too soon.

01:16:46.101 --> 01:16:46.810
I can see that.

01:16:46.893 --> 01:16:50.731
No, I'm not gonna do that

01:16:50.814 --> 01:16:51.857
with anybody.

01:16:51.940 --> 01:16:53.900
You mean ever?

01:16:53.984 --> 01:16:55.193
Well, with my husband of course.

01:16:55.277 --> 01:16:56.987
I mean, I'm not
entering a convent

01:16:57.070 --> 01:16:58.155
or anything for God's sake.

01:16:58.238 --> 01:17:00.198
It's just...

01:17:00.282 --> 01:17:03.869
for right now, for me,
life is complicated enough

01:17:03.952 --> 01:17:07.748
without getting involved
in a sexual relationship.

01:17:10.792 --> 01:17:14.838
So I guess driving to Vegas
is out of the question?

01:17:25.807 --> 01:17:28.352
Brian Mackelroy.

01:17:28.977 --> 01:17:30.979
Dylan McKay.

01:17:41.907 --> 01:17:42.741
What's this?

01:17:42.824 --> 01:17:44.868
Oh, a little leisure reading.

01:17:44.951 --> 01:17:46.870
<i>Byron, The Collected Works?</i>

01:17:46.953 --> 01:17:51.792
Mad, bad and dangerous to know.

01:17:51.875 --> 01:17:53.794
That was him and that's me.

01:17:59.841 --> 01:18:00.926
Daniel Messlier.

01:18:03.136 --> 01:18:04.971
Marissa Neimon.

01:18:07.974 --> 01:18:09.976
Jim Neigrant.

01:18:11.978 --> 01:18:13.980
Niku Rushdie.

01:18:16.024 --> 01:18:18.944
Steve Sanders.

01:18:30.997 --> 01:18:32.916
David Silver.

01:18:42.092 --> 01:18:43.844
Kelly Taylor.

01:18:56.022 --> 01:18:58.942
Janice Thall.

01:19:00.902 --> 01:19:03.280
Thomas Thatcher.

01:19:06.074 --> 01:19:08.702
Ronald Thindell.

01:19:08.785 --> 01:19:10.328
{\an1}Kelly, I never knew
you were so...

01:19:10.412 --> 01:19:11.246
Schmaltzy?

01:19:11.329 --> 01:19:14.124
{\an1}"Sentimental" is the word
I was looking for.

01:19:14.207 --> 01:19:16.668
No, you don't understand.

01:19:16.751 --> 01:19:18.295
My father's here.

01:19:18.378 --> 01:19:19.921
Where?

01:19:21.756 --> 01:19:23.925
Doreen Vantine.

01:19:27.095 --> 01:19:29.139
Elizabeth Walker.

01:19:31.099 --> 01:19:33.393
Brandon Walsh.

01:19:46.323 --> 01:19:48.742
Brenda Walsh.

01:19:55.916 --> 01:19:58.835
You just got to
understand Brenda,

01:19:58.919 --> 01:20:00.962
one minute you're my
little girl and then...

01:20:01.046 --> 01:20:03.673
all of a sudden you're
taking pregnancy tests.

01:20:06.760 --> 01:20:09.888
Things are moving kind
of fast for your old man.

01:20:09.971 --> 01:20:13.308
{\an1}Well, maybe I'm not
your little girl anymore.

01:20:18.688 --> 01:20:20.815
You'll always be my little girl.

01:20:32.160 --> 01:20:35.038
And last, but by no means least,

01:20:35.121 --> 01:20:36.122
Andrea Zuckerman.

01:20:40.001 --> 01:20:42.170
Congratulations, Andrea,

01:20:42.254 --> 01:20:43.755
and good luck at Yale.

01:20:43.838 --> 01:20:46.841
Thank you, Mr. Meyers--
I mean, Gil.

01:20:49.177 --> 01:20:51.930
Ladies and gentlemen,
the Class of 1993.

01:20:52.013 --> 01:20:55.058
(applause)

01:21:04.192 --> 01:21:06.319
(cheering)

01:21:14.369 --> 01:21:15.787
{\an1}BRANDON:
Steve, Steve?

01:21:15.871 --> 01:21:16.204
{\an1}What time is everybody
showing up tonight?

01:21:16.288 --> 01:21:18.623
Late, very late.

01:21:18.707 --> 01:21:19.791
AftCool.00.

01:21:19.875 --> 01:21:20.792
Dude, I am psyched.

01:21:20.875 --> 01:21:22.627
{\an1}It's grad night
and you graduated!

01:21:22.711 --> 01:21:24.921
Yes! Yes! Ah!

01:21:25.005 --> 01:21:25.922
CINDY:
Brandon, Steve.

01:21:26.006 --> 01:21:27.799
{\an1}BRANDON:
Come on.

01:21:27.882 --> 01:21:29.968
(shutter clicks)

01:21:30.051 --> 01:21:31.303
Come on, everybody.

01:21:31.386 --> 01:21:33.430
(all talking at once)

01:21:43.064 --> 01:21:45.692
Okay, okay.

01:21:50.697 --> 01:21:52.699
I'll be back.

01:22:05.295 --> 01:22:08.798
{\an1}Well, do you feel
any different?

01:22:08.882 --> 01:22:10.800
{\an3}Yeah, I do.

01:22:10.884 --> 01:22:12.844
It's not because
I got a diploma,

01:22:12.927 --> 01:22:15.180
and this will really
sound bizarre to you.

01:22:15.263 --> 01:22:16.014
I'm all ears.

01:22:16.097 --> 01:22:18.850
I had this
feeling all day,

01:22:18.933 --> 01:22:21.645
very strongly, that
Jack was with us.

01:22:21.728 --> 01:22:23.647
I could swear for a
minute that he was...

01:22:23.730 --> 01:22:25.231
he was talking to me.

01:22:25.315 --> 01:22:28.985
Well, maybe he was.

01:22:29.069 --> 01:22:30.862
{\an1}Let me get a picture
of you two.

01:22:35.784 --> 01:22:37.911
May I take one
of the three of you?

01:22:37.994 --> 01:22:39.913
Oh, I'd love it.red.

01:22:49.798 --> 01:22:51.716
Hey, how're you doing?

01:22:51.800 --> 01:22:52.258
Good.

01:22:52.342 --> 01:22:54.719
Guess where I'm going?

01:22:54.803 --> 01:22:56.054
Dinner with your mom?

01:22:56.137 --> 01:22:57.847
And my dad.

01:22:57.931 --> 01:22:58.431
Your dad?

01:22:58.515 --> 01:23:00.725
So that's
your dad?

01:23:00.809 --> 01:23:01.643
Yep, that's him.

01:23:01.726 --> 01:23:04.062
Now I know how I'm gonna
remember this day.

01:23:04.145 --> 01:23:07.232
It's the day I saw
my mom and my dad

01:23:07.315 --> 01:23:09.901
together in the same place.

01:23:22.330 --> 01:23:25.333
(phone ringing)

01:23:26.668 --> 01:23:27.877
CINDY:
Oh, let me guess.

01:23:27.961 --> 01:23:29.879
It was Brenda calling
to say, "Don't wait up."

01:23:29.963 --> 01:23:31.756
No, it was Dylan.

01:23:31.840 --> 01:23:33.633
He's coming over.

01:23:33.717 --> 01:23:36.094
Now? I mean, it's so late.

01:23:36.177 --> 01:23:37.887
He's coming over
in three minutes.

01:23:37.971 --> 01:23:40.640
He called from his
new cellular phone.

01:23:40.724 --> 01:23:41.599
Nothing quite as
disconcerting

01:23:41.683 --> 01:23:44.269
as the sight of a young
man with cash to burn.

01:23:44.352 --> 01:23:46.479
DYLAN:
<i>Did you ever notice</i>

01:23:46.563 --> 01:23:50.400
how people get
a little weird around money?

01:23:50.483 --> 01:23:51.568
Money'll do that to you.

01:23:51.651 --> 01:23:54.320
{\an1}Yeah, I'm not talking about
the person who gets the money.

01:23:54.404 --> 01:23:57.699
{\an1}I'm talking about
the people around him.

01:23:58.366 --> 01:24:00.827
Well, the biggest trap
that people fall into

01:24:00.910 --> 01:24:02.287
when they suddenly
find themselves

01:24:02.370 --> 01:24:05.915
in a higher
income bracket,

01:24:05.999 --> 01:24:07.375
they start acquiring
a lot of new possessions,

01:24:07.459 --> 01:24:11.296
and new people.

01:24:11.379 --> 01:24:15.425
In the process, they kind of
lose touch with who they were.

01:24:15.508 --> 01:24:19.804
{\an1}Hmm... that's not
gonna happen to me.

01:24:19.888 --> 01:24:21.639
I hope you're right.

01:24:21.723 --> 01:24:24.642
And to be sure...

01:24:24.726 --> 01:24:27.145
{\an1}I want to give
my money back to you.

01:24:28.271 --> 01:24:29.397
In the trust, like before.

01:24:31.399 --> 01:24:33.902
You mean you spent
all that energy

01:24:33.985 --> 01:24:35.862
trying to get the money
out of the trust

01:24:35.945 --> 01:24:37.489
and now you want
to put it back?

01:24:37.572 --> 01:24:40.033
{\an1}I want the same thing,
you know, I mean,

01:24:40.116 --> 01:24:41.326
{\an1}where I get a check every
month for my living expenses.

01:24:41.409 --> 01:24:45.205
{\an1}I just, uh... I'd like it
to be a little more.

01:24:45.288 --> 01:24:47.707
I can understand that.

01:24:47.791 --> 01:24:50.960
And, uh,
I need a sizeable advance.

01:24:51.044 --> 01:24:53.505
I think I'm gonna go bum around
Europe for most of the summer.

01:24:53.588 --> 01:24:55.965
And what about college?

01:24:56.049 --> 01:24:56.508
I don't know.

01:24:56.591 --> 01:24:57.342
I mean, I'm coming back.

01:24:57.425 --> 01:24:58.384
I suppose I'll get there
eventually.

01:24:58.468 --> 01:25:02.347
{\an1}I just,
I-I really need a break, Jim.

01:25:02.430 --> 01:25:03.389
I think Jack would understand.

01:25:06.309 --> 01:25:08.228
{\an1}So...

01:25:08.311 --> 01:25:09.646
you think the trust can be
reinstated?

01:25:11.731 --> 01:25:14.484
I think we can work it out.

01:25:14.567 --> 01:25:17.570
I must say
I'm pleasantly surprised.

01:25:17.654 --> 01:25:20.365
I was afraid that you
might fall into that trap.

01:25:20.448 --> 01:25:23.326
Well, if I ever do,
cut me off, all right?

01:25:23.409 --> 01:25:25.411
Last thing I need
right now is deep pockets.

01:25:25.495 --> 01:25:27.455
{\an1}So...

01:25:27.539 --> 01:25:29.249
if you'll excuse me,

01:25:29.332 --> 01:25:32.710
I got a date
with some fools on the hill.

01:25:32.794 --> 01:25:34.671
What are you guys
doing up there anyway?

01:25:34.754 --> 01:25:35.296
(chuckling):
You'll find out.

01:25:35.380 --> 01:25:38.883
You're as bad as Brandon.

01:25:38.967 --> 01:25:41.928
I'll take that as a compliment.

01:26:01.990 --> 01:26:05.368
Oh, boy.

01:26:05.451 --> 01:26:06.411
Wow, look at the view.

01:26:09.122 --> 01:26:11.291
{\an1}Wait, are you sure
this is the way?

01:26:11.374 --> 01:26:13.418
{\an1}Yeah. We just gotta
be careful.

01:26:13.501 --> 01:26:14.627
{\an3}Of what?

01:26:14.711 --> 01:26:16.546
Lions and tigers and bears.

01:26:16.629 --> 01:26:17.881
(laughing)

01:26:17.964 --> 01:26:19.382
{\an5}BOTH:
Lions and tigers
and bears, oh, my.

01:26:19.465 --> 01:26:22.886
Lions and tigers
and bears...

01:26:22.969 --> 01:26:24.762
Uh-oh.

01:26:24.846 --> 01:26:26.431
{\an4}BRANDON:
Hey, munchkins, glad
you could make it.

01:26:26.514 --> 01:26:28.349
We were about ready
to give up on you.

01:26:28.433 --> 01:26:29.267
{\an1}Well, we came
as soon as we could.

01:26:29.350 --> 01:26:31.811
Yeah, we left this
great club to come here.

01:26:31.895 --> 01:26:33.563
But we had to go
home and change first.

01:26:33.646 --> 01:26:34.564
Let's go get started.

01:26:34.647 --> 01:26:35.899
We already finished.

01:26:35.982 --> 01:26:37.734
You finished without me?

01:26:37.817 --> 01:26:38.735
Yeah, it wasn't so hard.

01:26:38.818 --> 01:26:40.612
Especially when Andrea
went up the embankment

01:26:40.695 --> 01:26:41.779
to set up the pulley.

01:26:41.863 --> 01:26:43.615
Yeah, I never knew
you were so nimble.

01:26:43.698 --> 01:26:45.867
Must be all my years
in the circus.

01:26:45.950 --> 01:26:46.576
You were in the circus?

01:26:46.659 --> 01:26:48.786
ANDREA:
No, I was kidding.

01:26:48.870 --> 01:26:50.455
Though I did have a lot
of circus dreams.

01:26:50.538 --> 01:26:53.708
Last fall when I kept having
to walk on that high wire.

01:26:53.791 --> 01:26:55.293
Wasn't that when you
were waiting to see

01:26:55.376 --> 01:26:56.127
if you got
accepted to Yale?

01:26:56.210 --> 01:26:58.296
No, that was
right before I applied.

01:26:58.379 --> 01:26:59.297
Are you still planning
on going, Andrea?

01:26:59.380 --> 01:27:01.799
Yeah.

